  "prompt": "Which sect of Jews lived in Macca and Madinah during the time of Prophet Muhammad?",
  "response": "During the time of Prophet Muhammad, several Jewish tribes lived in the Arabian Peninsula, particularly around the cities of Medina (previously known as Yathrib) and somewhat in the vicinity of Mecca. The most notable Jewish tribes in Medina included:\n\n1. **Banu Nadir**: One of the major Jewish tribes. They were involved in agriculture and owned property in Medina.\n2. **Banu Qurayza**: Another significant tribe known for their fortifications and involvement in the socio-economic structures of Medina.\n3. **Banu Qaynuqa**: A prominent tribe that was engaged in trade and craftsmanship.\n\nThese tribes had settled in the region for centuries and were involved in various socio-economic activities. Their interactions with the early Muslim community were complex, ranging from alliances to conflicts.",
